casebody.data:
October 10, 1949.

Per Curiam Decisions.

No. 89. Eastern Steamship Lines, Inc. v. Mulligan, Public Administrator. Arthur M. Boal for petitioner. George J. Engelman for respondent. Per Curiam:

The petition for writ of certiorari is granted. The judgment of the Court of Appeals is vacated and the case is remanded to that court for disposition in the light of Cosmopolitan Shipping Co. v. McAllister, 337 U. S. 783.
